Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.20,0:05:56.12,apollon main,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H101311&\bord0\shad0\fnRage Italic LET\fs30\blur0.5\frx8\fry352\pos(598,228)\frz357.293}Shirayuri
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.76,0:06:00.13,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,The coincidences keep on coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.84,0:06:02.20,apollon main,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,Even the name is similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.61,0:06:12.56,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, there's someone that I like.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.70,0:06:17.06,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,He's the only one I can think of right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.75,0:06:20.46,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm flattered by the way you feel about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.04,0:06:23.51,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm flattered, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.33,0:06:30.66,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.21,0:06:40.21,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,Sentaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.21,0:06:43.10,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hi. What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.10,0:06:44.91,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,You seem kinda troubled.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.91,0:06:46.84,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Here, eat this an' cheer up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.61,0:06:50.32,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,Sentaro, what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.05,0:06:54.01,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,I said something terrible to Kaoru.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.63,0:06:58.06,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,He might not come back here again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.33,0:07:07.78,apollon main,Sachiko,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.78,0:07:09.03,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Sachiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.72,0:07:10.74,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Do you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.74,0:07:13.62,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,know who it is that Ri'ko li...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:15.86,apollon main,Kota,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sleepy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.86,0:07:17.12,apollon main,Taichi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.85,0:07:19.10,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,N-Never mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.10,0:07:21.64,apollon main,Kota,0000,0000,0000,,School starts again today?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.09,0:07:24.57,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I-I can't ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.57,0:07:29.30,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to talk about anything romantic in this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.25,0:07:32.80,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Richie! It's been too long!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.22,0:07:35.97,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you come over for practice during winter vacation?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.97,0:07:38.47,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.37,0:07:49.15,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,Um... The teacher told me to give this to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.35,0:07:51.65,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.46,0:08:09.42,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Dad's finally come back,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.30,0:08:12.60,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,but everything seems so bleak right now
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.60,0:08:14.93,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,that I can't bring myself to talk about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.80,0:08:24.69,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Yo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.98,0:08:28.80,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Sen—What are you doing out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.80,0:08:30.69,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Richie! Get outta the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.10,0:08:38.37,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Richie, put a jacket on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.07,0:08:40.04,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.43,0:08:42.55,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.12,0:08:47.93,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Ri'ko's lonely without you around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.93,0:08:50.46,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, all you gotta do is stop by the shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.94,0:08:53.40,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going back there again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.19,0:08:56.75,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really mean that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.75,0:08:57.55,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.20,0:09:01.00,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Kaoru, got a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.91,0:09:07.09,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I heard a loud noise in here a minute ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.09,0:09:08.52,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.96,0:09:10.21,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.21,0:09:14.56,apollon main,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I wanted to give you this letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.56,0:09:15.72,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,A letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.72,0:09:18.24,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,It's from Shizu, our old housekeeper, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.24,0:09:21.71,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Shizu? Oh, that takes me back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.71,0:09:25.12,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,She wrote about your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.12,0:09:30.83,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,We've had our problems over the years,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.64,0:09:34.51,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,but it seems she happened to run into your mother in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.17,0:09:39.26,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,She got your mother's address and insisted I pass it on to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.63,0:09:42.63,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,We split up when you were little,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.63,0:09:46.02,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,so you might not remember her very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.34,0:09:52.02,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,But if you'd like to see her, then maybe you could go on your next break.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.58,0:09:56.25,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,I know this is sudden and may leave you at a loss,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.25,0:09:58.70,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,but whether you go or not is totally up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.04,0:10:02.72,apollon main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll let you get back to your studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.84,0:10:09.45,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Richie. You can take her some sweet rice treats as a souvenir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.45,0:10:12.63,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I never said I was going.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.73,0:10:14.71,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,You're not goin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.39,0:10:18.66,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just not up to it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.66,0:10:20.02,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,You moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.02,0:10:24.47,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,You'll regret it for the rest of your life if you pass up this chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.83,0:10:31.09,apollon main,Mariko,0000,0000,0000,,Kaoru?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.09,0:10:32.15,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.58,0:10:35.22,apollon main,Mariko,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing? I'm coming in!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.22,0:10:36.79,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.62,0:10:49.19,apollon main,Mariko,0000,0000,0000,,Kaoru, you're hiding something, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.19,0:10:50.63,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,No, not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.22,0:11:01.39,apollon main,Maruo,0000,0000,0000,,Blue trains?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.75,0:11:06.80,apollon main,Maruo,0000,0000,0000,,"Blue train" refers to the limited express trains from Asakaze
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.80,0:11:10.38,apollon main,Maruo,0000,0000,0000,,that have dedicated blue sleeper cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.20,0:11:13.90,apollon main,Maruo,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know that the design of the \Nfront and back car are different
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.90,0:11:16.48,apollon main,Maruo,0000,0000,0000,,because they have to switch between being the lead car?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.59,0:11:18.81,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.29,0:11:28.98,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, this is my\Nfirst time traveling alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.18,0:11:34.43,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Is it like a trip to help me get over my heartache?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.43,0:11:37.65,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You're late, Richie.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.65,0:11:40.97,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Y'know, it's a good thing I asked Maruo to get me a ticket!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.25,0:11:42.98,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.98,0:11:47.56,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I felt like takin' a trip to \NTokyo too, so I'm taggin' along!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.83,0:11:57.32,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I only went on this trip so I could be alone and think things over quietly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.70,0:12:01.70,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Man, travel an' frozen tangerines go together like bread an' butter!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.70,0:12:04.20,apollon main,Old Woman,0000,0000,0000,,I do have one more tangerine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.20,0:12:05.32,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Well, much obliged!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.01,0:12:08.87,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,They taste better before they thaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.80,0:12:11.87,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Damn that Maruo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.81,0:12:16.62,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, how can you afford this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.62,0:12:19.74,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I have money saved up from my part-time job.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.74,0:12:22.86,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,And then I sold some old records.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.86,0:12:25.14,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have nearly enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.45,0:12:29.30,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if I can make it to Jun's place,\NI'm sure it'll work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.30,0:12:32.52,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,What a thoughtless fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.59,0:12:39.07,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Here, this is yours, Richie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.26,0:12:43.06,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Ri'ko said the food in the dining car would probably be expensive
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.06,0:12:44.95,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,so she made these for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.71,0:12:50.78,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Ain't you gonna eat it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.25,0:12:55.58,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,She's been worried about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.07,0:13:21.73,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's with all these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.19,0:13:24.24,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a festival? Or a New Year's sale?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.24,0:13:26.74,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Tokyo Station is always like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.67,0:13:30.12,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go sightseeing around Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.64,0:13:34.32,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna see what your mom's like,\Nso I'm comin' with you.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:38.29,0:13:41.30,apollon main,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.5\shad0\bord0\i1\fs35\pos(633,86)\frx2\fry0\c&H779680&}Blue Butterfly
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.29,0:13:41.30,apollon main,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.5\shad0\bord0\i1\fs35\frx2\fry0\pos(635,88)\c&H344235&}Blue Butterfly
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.46,0:13:43.46,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the heck? This is some workplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.46,0:13:45.97,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, maybe I got the address wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.76,0:13:48.86,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,It's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.61,0:13:51.66,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's go in an' ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.66,0:13:53.01,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.85,0:13:56.64,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I've changed my mind about meeting her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.64,0:13:57.72,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Richie!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.72,0:14:00.55,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talkin' about?\NYou've come this far!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.55,0:14:02.50,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,It's better if I don't see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.50,0:14:04.82,apollon main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I did, I'm sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.45,0:14:08.33,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.51,0:14:17.95,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,She said it's your mom's day off today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.95,0:14:20.56,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Said she'd meet you here tomorrow afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.56,0:14:22.00,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,So we'll come back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.51,0:14:27.17,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I say we relax at Jun's place until then!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.35,0:14:36.43,apollon main,Okada,0000,0000,0115,,Do you two have business with Katsuragi Junichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.15,0:14:37.84,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0115,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.84,0:14:39.79,apollon main,Okada,0000,0000,0115,,There's no point in waiting for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.79,0:14:42.25,apollon main,Okada,0000,0000,0000,,He's been missing since last month.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.25,0:14:43.32,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.95,0:14:45.10,apollon main,Okada,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.10,0:14:50.20,apollon main,,0000,0000,0000,,Rumor has it he got in bad with some faction, and now he's in hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.20,0:14:54.53,apollon main,Okada,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that he's just shacking up with some girl, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.53,0:14:57.50,apollon main,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H010209&\shad0\bord0\fs30\blur0.75\fnOld newspaper font\b0\frz41.041\pos(586,307)}Fukahori Yurika
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.53,0:14:57.50,apollon main,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H010209&\shad0\bord0\fs30\blur0.75\fnOld newspaper font\b0\pos(994,444)\frz71.121\clip(m 1025 377 l 985 356 930 525 1012 538)}Fukahori Yurika
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.53,0:14:57.50,apollon main,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H010209&\shad0\bord0\fs30\blur0.75\fnOld newspaper font\b0\pos(830,448)\frz62.54\clip(m 865 389 l 770 472 753 530 824 546)}Fukahori Yurika
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.16,0:14:57.50,apollon main,Okada,0000,0000,0000,,That guy's popular with the college girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.50,0:15:01.03,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that doesn't surprise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.03,0:15:02.42,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Richie?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.42,0:15:03.50,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,No, not surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.19,0:15:08.63,apollon main,Okada,0000,0000,0000,,Have you two come all the way from Kyushu?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.24,0:15:16.22,apollon main,Hasegawa,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's make our guests from faraway Kyushu feel welcome! {too lazy to make this not sound terrible}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.60,0:15:18.35,apollon main,Okada,0000,0000,0000,,With shochu and water...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.35,0:15:20.35,apollon main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.91,0:15:22.84,apollon main,Okada,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.84,0:15:23.77,apollon main,Hasegawa,0000,0000,0000,,Water?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.55,0:15:32.86,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! You wouldn't \Nbelieve how stupid this guy is!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.34,0:15:35.85,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,He's always in some kind of trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.55,0:15:39.87,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm with him, his stupidity rubs off on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.20,0:15:43.08,apollon main,Okada,0000,0000,0000,,Good for you. You're lucky \Nto have such a good buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.33,0:15:47.23,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Buddy? Not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.23,0:15:49.00,apollon main,Okada,0000,0000,0000,,The best kind!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.00,0:15:51.09,apollon main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty rare to have a friend you can get goofy with.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.78,0:15:53.68,apollon main,Okada,0000,0000,0000,,Treasure him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.68,0:15:57.82,apollon main,Okada,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike love affairs, friendship is for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.65,0:16:21.71,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Kaoru?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.41,0:16:24.82,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You're Kaoru, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.88,0:16:29.25,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! What are you standing around like a scarecrow for?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.25,0:16:31.09,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You'll catch a cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.09,0:16:33.59,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing? Hurry up and come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.22,0:16:39.06,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.42,0:16:42.81,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I've never eaten curry this fancy before!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.81,0:16:45.96,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Go on. Don't be shy. Just eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.96,0:16:46.93,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.93,0:16:47.81,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.21,0:16:50.22,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I like the way you shovel it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.22,0:16:53.57,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a thing for men with a hearty appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.25,0:16:58.65,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,She's totally different from how I imagined her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.62,0:17:02.53,apollon main,Kaoru and Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.62,0:17:02.53,apollon 2nd,Kaoru and Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.54,0:17:06.20,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.20,0:17:08.30,apollon main,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother and son in perfect unison!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.30,0:17:09.58,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.69,0:17:12.98,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. He has no manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.98,0:17:14.70,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Is he a friend from school?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.70,0:17:19.09,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Or more like, we play music together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.09,0:17:21.91,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,He's a drummer, and I play the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.91,0:17:22.77,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Piano?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.27,0:17:26.87,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you used to love it when your dad played the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.85,0:17:31.02,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,He would play, and I'd sing along.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.74,0:17:35.78,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you were crying, you'd always stop and listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.11,0:17:40.28,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,That's such a happy memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.09,0:17:44.66,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really? I don't remember at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.06,0:17:48.52,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Dad never likes to talk about the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.87,0:17:51.32,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Of course he doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.32,0:17:54.67,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Who would want to talk about \Na washout of a mother like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.23,0:18:00.39,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the rain's stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.71,0:18:02.99,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna take a little stroll around Ginza.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.13,0:18:06.18,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I think he wanted to give us some time alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.77,0:18:09.52,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Better eat before it gets cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.16,0:18:26.43,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,It's this curry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.43,0:18:29.25,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,It's spicier than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.19,0:18:32.25,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Kaoru!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.69,0:18:35.49,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, how's school?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.49,0:18:37.21,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.21,0:18:39.56,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Have your eyes on any girls?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.78,0:18:42.93,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, did it not work out?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.93,0:18:46.60,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, I'd rather not talk about that right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.91,0:18:48.89,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,What, I'm right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.33,0:18:51.33,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.33,0:18:54.35,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Well, just the idea of the baby boy in my memory
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.35,0:18:58.61,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,who'd call me "Mama" and make gurgling noises... having a broken heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.22,0:19:00.91,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You're in the heyday of youth!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.70,0:19:09.37,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,A broken heart! Not bad, not bad at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.20,0:19:13.67,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! I'm lovelorn!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.94,0:19:18.02,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,The more I laughed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.02,0:19:21.26,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,the more whatever had been building up inside me disappeared into thin air.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.26,0:19:23.94,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,My mind emptied out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.42,0:19:30.27,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.64,0:19:33.23,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you weren't gonna make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.95,0:19:35.35,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.01,0:19:37.13,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,For me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.13,0:19:39.02,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,It's a jazz record.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.02,0:19:41.07,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,It's a song called "Lullaby of Birdland."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.32,0:19:43.83,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Listen and then try singing along to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.83,0:19:46.08,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come back to visit you again,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.66,0:19:49.44,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,so until then, I'd like you to practice that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.44,0:19:51.08,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,But this is in English, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.72,0:19:53.91,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know English at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.91,0:19:57.26,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be fine. Just imitate what you hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.26,0:20:01.59,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Jazz sounds best when it's sung by a woman with a husky voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.75,0:20:06.10,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come back for sure, so practice for me, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.67,0:20:08.60,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Kaoru... Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.86,0:20:12.65,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.74,0:20:18.11,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I thought... I'd probably never see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.39,0:20:20.59,apollon main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I told myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.33,0:20:36.88,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Why did my mom leave me behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.76,0:20:44.14,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Those words that I couldn't ask flew away somewhere with this scenery.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.15,0:20:49.28,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Mom's mouth formed the words, "I'm sorry."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.39,0:20:55.40,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,I shook my head, but I'm not sure she saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.45,0:20:57.90,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.28,0:21:00.99,apollon main,Ritsuko,0000,0000,0000,,That was heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.58,0:21:08.91,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Ri'ko!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.60,0:21:10.70,apollon main,Sen,0000,0000,0000,,Where were ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.08,0:21:17.25,apollon main,Kaoru,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Ri.
